Laser.SetVelocityCompensation allows to change the average laser power property in real-time based on the simulated velocity of the scanners. This command is useful because the velocity of the spot slows down as the galvos trace out an arc or sharp corner since the galvos cannot instantaneously change speed or direction. Too low a marking speed however, may result in an excessive mark depth or burning particularly in the corners where only partial penetration may be desired.
Velocity Compensation mode. Available options are: Disabled Dutycycle - Limit: 10% - 80% Frequency - Limit: 10kHz - 100kHz Power - Limit: 10% - 80%
